---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import CodeBlock from '../components/CodeBlock.astro';
import FeatureCard from '../components/FeatureCard.astro';
import SectionHeader from '../components/SectionHeader.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Glovebox" description="A sandboxed Docker environment that actually feels like home. Your shell, your editor, your workflow—running safely inside a container.">

  <!-- Hero Section -->
  <section class="py-20 lg:py-32 grid-bg">
    <div class="container-wide">
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto text-center">
        <!-- Hero illustration -->
        <div class="mb-10 flex justify-center">
          <img
            src="/glovebox/hero-glovebox.png"
            alt="Glovebox - Sandboxed development environment illustration"
            class="w-full max-w-md h-auto"
          />
        </div>

        <h1 class="text-4xl lg:text-5xl font-medium leading-tight mb-6">
          AI assistants run code.<br/>
          <span class="text-muted">So does npm install.</span>
        </h1>

        <p class="text-xl text-muted leading-relaxed mb-10 max-w-2xl mx-auto">
          Glovebox gives you a sandbox that actually feels like home. Your shell, your editor, your workflow—running safely inside a container with your project mounted.
        </p>

        <div class="mb-8 max-w-lg mx-auto">
          <CodeBlock code="brew install joelhelbling/glovebox/glovebox" />
        </div>

        <a href="/glovebox/docs/getting-started/" class="btn-primary">
          Get Started
          <svg class="w-5 h-5 ml-2" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2">
            <path d="M5 12h14M12 5l7 7-7 7"/>
          </svg>
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Why Glovebox Section -->
  <section class="py-20 lg:py-24">
    <div class="container-narrow">
      <SectionHeader title="Why Glovebox" />

      <div class="prose prose-lg text-muted leading-relaxed space-y-6">
        <p>
          AI coding assistants are powerful—but they run code. So do npm packages, pip installs, and that shell script you found on Stack Overflow. Running untrusted code on your development machine is a calculated risk.
        </p>

        <p>
          You could spin up a VM. You could fight with container configs every time. But that kills your flow.
        </p>

        <p>
          <strong class="text-ink">Glovebox is a sandboxed Docker environment that actually feels like yours.</strong> Configure it once with the shell, editor, and tools you want. Run it in any project. Your environment travels with you, safely isolated from your host machine.
        </p>

        <p class="text-ink italic border-l-4 border-teal pl-4">
          Think of it as glamping on Jurassic Island: even in mortal danger, you still get your Nespresso.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Features Section -->
  <section class="py-20 lg:py-24 bg-white/50">
    <div class="container-wide">
      <SectionHeader title="Features" />

      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
        <FeatureCard
          title="Composable Mods"
          description="Mix and match shells, editors, languages, and AI tools. Build exactly the environment you want from reusable pieces."
          icon="/glovebox/icon-composable-mods.png"
        />
        <FeatureCard
          title="Layered Images"
          description="Build your base environment once. Extend it per-project with additional tools. No redundant rebuilds."
          icon="/glovebox/icon-layered-images.png"
        />
        <FeatureCard
          title="Persistent Containers"
          description="Your changes survive between sessions. Install something ad-hoc, it's still there tomorrow."
          icon="/glovebox/icon-persistent-containers.png"
        />
        <FeatureCard
          title="Commit Workflow"
          description="Made changes you want to keep? Glovebox detects them and offers to commit them back to the image."
          icon="/glovebox/icon-commit-workflow.png"
        />
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Quick Start Section -->
  <section class="py-20 lg:py-24">
    <div class="container-narrow">
      <SectionHeader title="Quick Start" />

      <div class="space-y-8">
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-lg font-medium mb-4">One-time setup:</h3>
          <CodeBlock code={`glovebox init --base    # Select your OS, shell, editor, tools
glovebox build --base   # Build the base image`} />
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3 class="text-lg font-medium mb-4">Then, in any project:</h3>
          <CodeBlock code={`cd ~/projects/my-app
glovebox run`} />
          <p class="mt-4 text-muted">
            You're inside a sandboxed container. Your project is mounted at <code class="text-sm bg-black/5 px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded font-mono">/workspace</code>. Your shell, your editor, your tools—all there. When you exit, your container persists. When you return, it's waiting.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3 class="text-lg font-medium mb-4">Clean up when needed:</h3>
          <CodeBlock code="glovebox clean --all" />
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Is This For Me Section -->
  <section class="py-20 lg:py-24 bg-white/50">
    <div class="container-narrow">
      <SectionHeader title="Is This For Me?" />

      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-12">
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-lg font-medium text-teal mb-4">Glovebox is for you if:</h3>
          <ul class="space-y-3 text-muted">
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-teal flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2">
                <path d="M5 13l4 4L19 7"/>
              </svg>
              <span>You run AI coding assistants and want to limit the blast radius</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-teal flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2">
                <path d="M5 13l4 4L19 7"/>
              </svg>
              <span>You connect MCP servers or other tools that reach into your filesystem</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-teal flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2">
                <path d="M5 13l4 4L19 7"/>
              </svg>
              <span>You evaluate npm packages, pip installs, or random scripts before trusting them</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-teal flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2">
                <path d="M5 13l4 4L19 7"/>
              </svg>
              <span>You prefer vim, emacs, or neovim over VS Code</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-teal flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2">
                <path d="M5 13l4 4L19 7"/>
              </svg>
              <span>You think in tmux panes or zellij tabs</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-teal flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2">
                <path d="M5 13l4 4L19 7"/>
              </svg>
              <span>You want consistent environments across projects without VM overhead</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-teal flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2">
                <path d="M5 13l4 4L19 7"/>
              </svg>
              <span>You're a hacker (in the good, MIT sense) who experiments with hazardous things</span>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3 class="text-lg font-medium text-warning mb-4">Glovebox is not:</h3>
          <ul class="space-y-3 text-muted">
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-warning flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2">
                <path d="M6 18L18 6M6 6l12 12"/>
              </svg>
              <span>Infrastructure for production environments</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-warning flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2">
                <path d="M6 18L18 6M6 6l12 12"/>
              </svg>
              <span>A security solution for deployed code</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-warning flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2">
                <path d="M6 18L18 6M6 6l12 12"/>
              </svg>
              <span>A replacement for proper sandboxing in CI/CD</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-warning flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2">
                <path d="M6 18L18 6M6 6l12 12"/>
              </svg>
              <span>A GUI-first experience</span>
            </li>
          </ul>

          <p class="mt-6 text-muted italic">
            Glovebox is a personal workbench tool. It doesn't go in your code and doesn't run on your server. It's the sealed chamber on your workbench where you safely handle the unknown.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

</BaseLayout>
